26/06/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski and his Serbia-Montenegro counterpart, Svetozar Marovic, agreed on Saturday (25 June) that the two countries should further develop economic co-operation and collaborate within the context of the EU integration process.
The two met during Crvenkovski's visit to Montenegro.
They stressed that bilateral ties were very good and should not be affected by problems in relations between churches in Belgrade and Skopje.
On Friday, Crvenkovski met with Montenegrin counterpart Filip Vujanovic and announced plans to open a consulate in Podgorica on 1 September.
(Makfax, Telma TV - 25/06/05;
A1 TV - 24/06/05)
